cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about training word embeddings for multiple languages and using them for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of the embeddings, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions investigating the semantic features captured by the embeddings, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
